# Recipe To-Dos

18 to-dos, 5 points each, with 5 extra credit to-dos

## Essential

### Code
`35 points`

- [x] Use of lowercase alphabet for all markup, style, and file and folder names (also `class`, `id`, and file and folder names should not have spaces, instead use a hyphen `-` or an underscore `_` in place of a space). For example, `<section id="more-recipes">` instead of `<section id="More Recipes">`; `main.css` instead of `Main.CSS`
- [x] Use of semantic section (`header`, `nav`, `section`, etc.) and semantic text-level elements (`strong`, `em`, `time`, etc.)
  - See HTML5 Doctor’s [HTML5 Element Index](http://html5doctor.com/#glossary)
- [x] Use of semantic grouping elements `ol`,` ul`, or `dl` for organizing lists instead of a `table`
- [x] Use of CSS box model properties `padding`, `border`, and `margin` for spacing and rule elements
- [x] Use of an external stylesheet via the `link` element
  - For example: `<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/main.css">`
- [x] Use of `rel="canonical"` to cite original source of content
  - For example: `<link rel="canonical" href="https://mooshujenne.com/czech-goulash-cesky-gulas/">`
- [x] Use of a meaningful `title` and `meta` description
  - For example: `<title>`Easy Ramen Recipe!`</title>`
  - For example: `<meta name="description" content="Get the feeling of authentic handmade ramen at home with ease!">`

### Design
`35 points`

- [x] Use of web safe fonts, see [CSS font stacks](http://www.cssfontstack.com) for fallback replacements
- [x] Use of [web safe colors](http://websafecolors.info), please use short-hex values
  - For example: `#ff0033` becomes `#f03`
  - See also [Web Safe Color Chart](https://htmlcolorcodes.com/color-chart/)
- [x] Use of a cohesive [color palette](https://htmlcolorcodes.com/color-chart/) for uniting typography, borders, background colors, and imagery
- [x] Use of [typographic characters](http://htmlarrows.com) for fractions ½ , degrees (fahrenheit) ℉, arrows ⤴, etc.
- [] Use of `nav` to navigation to page sections (fragments) `#ingredients`, `#directions`, etc.
- [x] Small screen, mobile first, single-column layout
- [x] Use of `float` based columns and media queries `@media` or Bootstrap ([Grid system](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/layout/grid/)) for responsive layout — small-to-wide-to-wider screens

###  Validate
`20 points`

- [x] [Validate HTML](https://validator.w3.org) _(no errors; warnings are ok, but try to resolve)_
  - Use CSS instead of `<center>` or `align="center"` and other [obsolete and deprecated elements](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element#Obsolete_and_deprecated_elements) and [attributes](https://css-tricks.com/list-of-depreciated-elements-still-in-widespread-use/)
- [x] [Validate CSS](http://jigsaw.w3.org/css-validator/) _(no errors; warnings are ok, but try to resolve)_
  - Only validate `main.css` (exclude bootstrap.css)

### Git
`10 points`

- [x] Repo should contain only essential files:
  - `index.html`
  - `css` (folder containing an external stylesheet)
    - For example: `main.css`
  - `img` (folder containing images)
    - For example: `jiffy-cornbread.jpg`
  - `versions` (folder [no spaces] containing tests, experiments, work in progress, etc.)
    - For example: `recipe-test-1.html`
  - `comps` (folder containing images (screen-shots) and/or comps used as style references)
    - For example: `style-idea-1.pdf`
    - Or include a list of references in the `README.md`
  - `README.md`
    - Update this file with a proper heading (title) and paragraph (description)
    - Markdown [basic](http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/basics) and [dingus](http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/dingus)
- [x] Add a [description and url](https://i.imgur.com/CexeWBQ.gif) to your GitHub repo
  - Example description: _A tasty HTML & CSS recipe._
  - Example url: `https://jgagne.github.io/html-css-recipe/`

## Extra Extra
`25 points`

- [] Use of original artwork (photography, illustration, etc.) with inclusion of credit byline
  - Credit byline example: `<figcaption><small class="photo-credit">Photo by Jane Doe</small></figcaption>`
- [] Test color contrast ratio of your webpage meets WCAG guidelines via [Accessible Colors](http://accessible-colors.com) `#useful`
- [x] Save images for web, using Photoshop’s `Export > Save for Web (Legacy)…` feature by exporting images at a width of `960px` using the `JPEG High Preset`, and then use [ImageOptim](https://imageoptim.com) to save a few more KB. _(Ideal file size per non-retina image should be under `200 KB`.)_
- [] Use of a web font for headings using the `@font-face` rule to progressively enhance the existing web safe CSS font stack
- [] Use of [smooth-scroll](https://github.com/cferdinandi/smooth-scroll) JavaScript, for navigation links, to add smooth page scrolling
